<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> indemnify someone against something • indemnify someone for something</xh5><p> <i>indemnify someone against something—</i>provide protection against possible loss or damage: A system of insurance must be devised, which shall <u>indemnify them against</u> all the accidents and reverses of life.</p><p> <i>indemnify someone for something—</i>pay compensation to a person for loss or damage actually suffered: I will <u>indemnify you for</u> any expenses you may incur on my behalf.</p> </entry>
